ascent.name: Les specialistes
ascent.comment: Quel plaisir de faire cette voie, première séance depuis 1 an et demi, il faisait chaud, à la journée (2h de bagnole aller et 2h retour). Pas vraiment idéal mais pour une fois ça fonctionne facilement. Ca change des mois et des mois de galère à rien faire. C'est pas extrême mais c'est juste une voie Mythique! et pour 8b+, c'est bien calibré. Merci à Alex!

ascent.name: Silmarillion
ascent.comment: Nothing comes together on this trip :(

ascent.name: La toile à Berthe
ascent.comment: J'aimerais dédier cette voie à un original au grand coeur, parti bien trop tôt qui restera toujours notre Momo du Windstein.

ascent.name: Kong Harald
ascent.comment:
Kanskje den fineste i Loddis så langt! Pumpende og buldrete på en gang. Ganske hard
4 økter?

ascent.name: What's The Scoop
ascent.comment: Best line at b rock? Somewhat of a low start to cutting edge, only shares the final move. Psyched to get this one done after lots of work in the heat!! On to the next!!

ascent.name: Importárú direkt
ascent.comment: Importárú és a direkt kiszálló (7B+?) Peremre nyúlós CS bétával a kunsztnál. Szerintemönmagában az import a peremre nyúlós bétával a vállas megoldás helyett inkább 7C+, de direkt kiszállóval már 8A. A vállás béta és a direkt kiszálló pedig 8A+ lehet tényleg (Primőr Importárú)  Jó kis boulder mindenesetre :)

ascent.name: Brown dampness
ascent.comment: Fits my stile and size perfectly, 2 sessions. Not sure about the grade but I don't have the right experience

ascent.name: Dream Snatcher
ascent.comment: "Don't punt!" Good day with the broski.

ascent.name: Canindé de Baixo
ascent.comment: Cair no final do boulder já está virando meu karma!! Depois de perder algumas vezes no agarrão, finalmente consegui ficar e encadenar meu primeiro V dois dígitos!! V10 clássico demais!!

ascents.name: Carolina Crocker and the Tipple of Doom
Pudd's pretty dress
ascents.comment: Rad route, tricky ending when your pumped and trying to warm up.  Props to Danno for starting the send train.  Highly recommended

ascents.name: Way Up Yonder
ascents.comment: Lots of holds, find the ones that work for you, go to the second set of anchors

ascents.name: The Machine Shop
ascents.comment: Burly overhanging arete to slab boulder problem, what can be better

ascents.name: Unknow
ascents.comment: 4 Big moves in a row on jugs

ascents.name: Climax control
ascents.comment: Excellent, Beware the move guarding the anchors, travisty is next

ascents.name: Red Bull
ascents.comment: Classic New River Gorge climbing. Crimpers, mantles, scary clip. etc.

ascents.name: West Virginia Two Step
ascents.comment: Bouldery and crimpy, should have tried for the flash...

ascents.name: Creature
ascents.comment: Fun climbing to a confussion crux, should have flashed had there been direction arrows after the crux

ascents.name: triple sec
ascents.comment: Fun route, soft for the grade

ascents.name: Buisnes Up front party in the back
Bosnian Vacation
ascents.comment: Bouldery start to slab to steep.....

ascents.name: Crimps on the Barby
ascents.comment: Excellent route, and yes all the draws are danglers.  Gotta sack up for the crux....

ascents.name: Crossing the Line
ascents.comment: Fun times in the fall sun, would have sent second go, but allas, many days and many falls I finally found the anchors

ascents.name: Spank
ascents.comment: If this was a verticle wall and all the hold were incut it would be 5.9

ascents.name: Belly of The Beast
ascents.comment: If you are as short as Chris Hill the first moves are the hard part....

ascents.name: Hellraiser
ascents.comment: I love slopers, especially when they are 10 feet off the ground and there is 5.11 climbing afterword

ascents.name: Game Theory
ascents.comment: Excellent route, if this were at endless there would be fixed draws

ascents.name: Superstition
ascents.comment: Excellent, would be 12d if there was loads of Friction

ascents.name: Reckless Abandon
ascents.comment: Did it out right before the hold broke, did it out right after the hold broke, not much difference in grade

ascents.name: Trebuchet
ascents.comment: Most Excellent Rock Climb. Power endurance through and through. Fall is Guuuud

ascents.name: Cock diesel
ascents.comment: Most excellent route.  Kind of like chills mom, hard to get through but once you know how to do it, it's not that bad

ascents.name: High Yeller
ascents.comment: Great Rock, to choss band to bullet white sandstone with a tenuos crux on slab...what slab at the cirque????

ascents.name: The Project
ascents.comment: Finally, all that winter bouldering is paying off...

ascents.name: Old Scratch
ascents.comment: Bouldery, to rest, bouldery to rest, bouldery then clip chains

ascents.name: Carolina Crocker and the Tipple of Doom
new World order
ascents.comment: Old mans repeat...in the full summer sun...

ascents.name: Humpty Pumpty
ascents.comment: Fun climb on bullet limestone, classic clip and slip on go 2, took 2 more tries to get the nerves back in line for the send

ascents.name: Buzz Kill
ascents.comment: 3 goes...fell at second bolt (doh!) 2nd go, pulle drope then fired the rig...thin...thin...thin

ascents.name: Albatross
ascents.comment: Very short...if you like bouldering on crimps and poor feet, get on it!

ascents.name: Stunning the Hog
ascents.comment: Wow...in a full on snow storm!!!

ascents.name: To Defy The Laws of Tradition
nightmare
ascents.comment: a bit loose...of the more than 50 holds, I only broke 2 of them...one almost crushing matt fanning, and the other a really good foot mid crus.  Either way, slick, like the rest of Seneca but interesting and fun!

ascents.name: The Lightness
ascents.comment: Super rad route with excellent movement throught he crux...

ascents.name: Gone Sniffin'
ascents.comment: Man what a route...super pumped at the end..foot cutting..grunting and maybe a woop woop going for the chains!!!

ascents.name: Gold Toof
ascents.comment: Wow...let Joe "the sleeping wonderkid" Gruss snag the first ascent...its all good though, one of the best at Old House...great weekend with great friends...way hot but 5 new lines have steel in them!

ascents.name: Michael Boltin'
ascents.comment: Holy cow this thing is great!!

ascents.name: Questlove
ascents.comment: Sent 3rd go after breaking the crux hold...
